## Lesson 7: Edge Detection 
<img src="https://images.code.org/ef660fedce89a5ee70046bcf7762855e-image-1715009802151.png" alt="sketch of a daisy" width="200px" style="border-radius:10px; float:right; margin: 0 20px 40px 40px;">

#### This lesson focuses on **developing algorithms** that help computers identify and outline distinct boundaries within images. 

#### Students engage in activities that involve writing and optimizing their own **edge detection algorithms** and discussing their efficiency and practical applications.

#### By the end of this lesson, students should understand the technical aspects and importance of edge detection in various computer vision tasks.


